# Project Conventions

## Core Stack

- Frontend UI framework: Material UI (MUI)
- Styling overrides: SCSS classes for custom visual adjustments
- Database: Prisma

## Module Architecture

- Business logic belongs in root-level module folders under `modules/`.
- Each module has its own folder: `modules/<module-name>/`.
- The `apps/web` app should import and compose module functionality, but should not be the primary home of business logic.
- Keep `apps/web` focused on routing, composition, and app shell concerns.

## Frontend Structure

- Use MUI components as the default UI primitives.
- Use SCSS classes to override or extend visual styling when needed.
- Keep style overrides local and explicit; avoid global one-off CSS hacks.

## Data Layer

- Use Prisma for database access.
- Keep data access patterns module-oriented (inside module folders), not scattered across unrelated app files.
